      "author": "Brightwav3",
      "description": "First public release of Advanced Bases: three lightweight, Notion-style views for Obsidian Bases.\n\n## Views\n- **Cards Compact** — a native-Cards-style card layout with a Compact toggle for a leaner icon+title+pills row layout.\n- **Feed** — a scrolling feed of full note previews with lazy rendering and an optional \"New note\" button.\n- **Timeline** — a Gantt-style timeline with date-grouped lanes, per-lane colors, and Ctrl+scroll zoom.\n\nEvery view has a \"?\" help button in the Bases toolbar with a quick reference for its controls. Localized into 15 languages.\n\n## Installation\nManual install: download `main.js`, `manifest.json`, and `styles.css` below into `<vault>/.obsidian/plugins/advanced-bases/`, then enable the plugin in Settings → Community plugins.",
